The paper discusses techniques for activity recognition and dynamic texture recognition, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) communities. The use of symbolic approximation and piece-wise aggregation also suggests a potential connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT).
